          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td>
      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
        <tr>
          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chpurple"><font class="h1font"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Correct Manners of Play<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.50)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=10153'>Kyle "-ThrillKill-" Tsetso</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=10153&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 26, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> <b>Introduction</b><br>
<br>
Often times a topic such as this is immediately dismissed. &quot;Bah, I know how to play the game.&quot; you might be saying to yourself as you click &quot;Back&quot; on your browser.<br>
<br>
But do you really?<br>
<br>
It may seem odd for me to bring up this topic, but it might amaze you to hear how often a player makes his opponent feel uncomfertable, or insults them. Sometimes without even knowing it. Want to correct this behavior? Read on.<br>
<br>
<b>Beginning the Game</b><br>
<br>
There is no need to be overly hospitible about it, but there&#39;s also no need to be rude or big-headed. Put forward some humor, attempt to make even the most serious of games an enjoyable one by showing that you think of it only as a game. And you should, because that is all that it is. It is meant to be fun. So smile, offer a handshake before the match begins, or just be polite. There&#39;s no point in sitting down to play if you do not intend to enjoy the game you are about to delve into.<br>
<br>
<b>Maintaining A Friendly Atmosphere</b><br>
<br>
Instead of frowning and mumbling after your intricate plan is thwarted by your opponent, smile and compliment their abilities. Think of it this way: You will be prepared next time. As a player, you must be prepared to expand and evolve your skills. To broaden your horizen and alter your deck accordingly. Perhaps in stopping one of your strategies in its tracks, your opponent left themselves open for another approach. And even then, should your next plan succeed be sure to continue upholding the friendly atmosphere. Crack jokes whenever possible. It isn&#39;t that hard.<br>
<br>
Sometimes you can hurt a players confidence by making the most harmless statements. Something you may not even consider offensive might turn out to be just that, so unless you&#39;re playing with someone you know enough, try to watch what you say. And if you do make remarks that could be taken the wrong way, make sure your opponent knows you&#39;re just joking. You may be surprised to find out how seemingly small things could hurt someone&#39;s feelings so badly.<br>
<br>
<b>Finishing A Well-Played Game</b><br>
<br>
Lady Luck has either smiled upon you, or spanked you so hard your children will walk bowl-legged, but either result should not effect your mood too greatly. There are two main types of &quot;bad&quot;.<br>
<br>
<i>The Bad Winner</i>: Often sighted celebrating quite audiobly, merrily speaking ill of their opponents skills and abilities. These are among the worst in games, as it drives away individuals from competing with others. Sometimes everyone altogether. Driving a potential player away from the game by belittling them for your own personal gain is not an honorable path.<br>
<br>
<i>The Bad Loser</i>: Suffering a loss is indeed disheartening, but you must remember to stree this simple fact to yourself: This is just a game. It is meant to be fun. And the moment you lose sight of that is the moment you should stop playing. See your defeat as an opportunity for growth. In other words, learn from your mistakes. You&#39;ll do better next time. I promise.<br>
<br>
<b>In Conclusion...</b><br>
<br>
Yup, Magi-Nation is an excellent game. Though some may contest this statement, I feel that it is indeed true. This game is as unique as any other, but at the same time it is just like the rest. Play it as you would play any other game, whether it&#39;s a CCG within the walls of a collectibles shop, or soccer with your friends in your backyard, it is just a game. Remember that.<br>
<br>
No one is perfect. I freely admit I sometimes do not take my own advice, but it&#39;s a personal trait I am actively working on. Being a better player doesn&#39;t always mean you&#39;re better at the game. It also means your the kind of player people enjoy playing with in the first place. So good luck, have fun, and eat plenty of sandwhiches.<br>
<br>
... yeah, when I wrote this I was pretty hungry. :P <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/magination/articles/articles.php?id=3820&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/magination/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></td></tr></table></td>
